parameters.description: Ion velocity in s/c z direction - vi_z - app. horizontal

parameters.description: -------------------> Vertical velocity (positive in the Y-axis direction)

parameters.description: Horizontal velocity in corotatingEarth frame (positive eastward)

parameters.description: Horizontal velocity in corotating Earth frame after WATSCOR correction

parameters.description: GCI position vector of DE spacecraft in kilometers.

parameters.description: GCI velocity vector of DE spacecraft in km/sec.

parameters.description: GCI spin axis unit vector of DE spacecraft.

parameters.name: h_flux
parameters.description: H+ number flux, at 15 energies (~0.01 to ~20keV) and 14 pitch angles (6 shown)

parameters.name: h_uncertainty
parameters.description: ---> ONE Standard deviation of H+ number flux at 15 energy and 14 pitch angle bins.

parameters.name: o_flux
parameters.description: O+ number flux, at 15 energies (~0.01 to ~20keV) and 14 pitch angles (6 shown)

parameters.name: o_uncertainty
parameters.description: ---> ONE Standard deviation of O+ number flux at 15 energy and 14 pitch angle bins.

parameters.name: he_flux
parameters.description: He+ number flux, at 15 energies (~0.01 to ~20keV) and 14 pitch angles (6 shown)

parameters.name: he_uncertainty
parameters.description: ONE Standard deviation of He+ number fluxat 15 energy and 14 pitch angle bins.

parameters.name: INTERPOLATED_BACKGROUND
parameters.description: Background count rate interpolated to center time. scalar

parameters.name: STANDARD_DEVIATION_OF_INTERPOLATED_BACKGROUND
parameters.description: ---> One standard deviation of Interpolated Background. scalar

parameters.name: Low_energy_cut_off
parameters.description: Lowest Energy above the spacecraft potential accepted. scalar

parameters.name: Mode_error_flag
parameters.description: Bitwise combination of  He_data,N_flag, C_flag, A_flag, Noisy_flag, Short_flag, and PA_coverage_flag. scalar

parameters.name: He_data
parameters.description: He+ data available flag 0=data for he+; 1=no he+ data

parameters.name: N_flag
parameters.description: ---> Data valid flag 0=good; 1=Not available or use with caution

parameters.name: C_flag
parameters.description: ---> Sun Pulse Flag0=good; 1=use data from the lowest energy channel with caution.

parameters.name: A_flag
parameters.description: ---> Attitude Available Flag 0: Source data CAN provide sensor orientation relative to the spacecraft velocity. 1: CAN NOT

parameters.name: Noisy_flag
parameters.description: ---> Supplemental Data Valid Flag #1 0=good; 1= Telemetry interval contains unphysically high signal levels

parameters.name: Short_flag
parameters.description: ---> Supplemental Data Valid Flag #2 0=good; 1=Too short to evaluate data quality.

parameters.name: PA_coverage_flag
parameters.description: ---> Pitch Angle Coverage Flag 0=good; 1=Incomplete PA coverage.

parameters.name: Geographic_position
parameters.description: Geographic Position Altitude above the geoid, latitude and longitude.

parameters.name: Geomagnetic_position
parameters.description: Geomagnetic Position Magnetic local time, Invariant latitude and geomagnetic latitude.
